76561198075978775,Recommended,244770,21590769,"Posted: 2 March, 2016",all,XIN_FTW,"Starmade is everything you want in an epic Sci-Fi space builder sim, minus the shiny graphics and story.1. Have an actual avatar 1st and 3rd person view, not just the inside of a cockpit2. Build your ship/station/home world/mech in Creative or Survival modes3. Create your faction/empire/rebel fleet4. Travel from space to planet surface and back without load screens5. Massive Universe...planets/sectors/solar systems/multiple galaxies...you will die of old age before exploring it all6. Single player or Join one of many Worldwide Multiplayer Servers PVE/PVP/RP7. Simple or complex Builds, your choice. With indepth logic blocks and functions for the dedicated builder8. Advanced build mode with adjustable quantity line/plane/cube function, multi axis symmetry build, rotation etc.9. Blueprints for saving creations, allowing you to respawn, trade, download from or upload to the community site10. Pre-existing NPC enemies and  AI modules so you can create your own enemies/allies...There is so much to this game that you really just need to try it. The possibilities are almost endless for those with a healthy imagination.Starmade is often compared to Minecraft graphically, though it has a much greater selection of block types available. Of course cubes are a given, it is voxel based afterall, but with wedges, corners and their variants your builds can be very sleek. This is the game you should graduate to when you get bored of Minecrafts limitations.If you simply can not deal with anything less than cinematic style realistic graphics then this game is likely not for you. Try out Empyrion or Space Engineers, both great games, but the trade off is you sacrifice the scope of the game environment.Sorry fans of Mass Effect and Half Life, but if you are looking for a deep engaging story with fully realized characters and plot, this is not your game.  But if you want to let your imagination loose and create your own story, your own universe alone or with friends then Starmade might be your flavour.You will spawn into a universe with some inventory to get you going and a limitless expanse of space stretching out before you.If your first reaction is to look for someone to tell you what to do next, go back to the Steam Store and keep hunting, this is not your game.But if you see that epic expanse, and excitement fills your heart with the desire to explore, build and test the limitations of your imagination....welcome to the family!Basically put.When you were a child, if you saw a cardboard box and had a million ideas of what you could do with it and not one of them included storage, you will love Starmade."
