76561197999709326,Not Recommended,244770,26198383,"Posted: 24 October, 2016",all,Balthazar,"In case you missed it: DEMO IS FULL GAME. DOWNLOAD DEMO = FREE FULL GAME (currently)If you want to make startrek/wars/whatever replicas this game is incredible. It has hands down the best tools for building in any voxel game i've seen; copy/pasting sections, placing large lines/circles/boxes/cylinders with ease, saving and loading ships/turrets/drones is quick once you know how, and building basic ships is extremely easy; only more advanced design aspects like weapon slaving, logic and moving components really require looking up information online. There are also tools for importing and exporting ships as 3D models. In addition the engine's performance is quite solid, i'm on a 5 year old machine and it can still handle 500m ships duking it out, 100s of drones or mining ships eating entire asteroids in one go. It has problems in some cases, like thousands of homing missiles, but it's generally well optimized with a few hiccups still in the game.So why, with all these great things and 2000 hours ingame am i not recommending this?Every single mechanic in the game is a broken mess. All the weapons are imballanced, to the point where of the 300+ weapon combinations only about 5 are actually useful. As far as survival/progression goes the game has nothing to do. You can create any item in the game in a few minutes at most from starting out, and once you get larger miners going resource collecting is utterly trivial. All the factories in the game are made from generic materials or bought for 1% of your starting money so forget about making any kind of intricate factories. And it's been like this for 2 years now.The game is early alpha and these things would normally be expected to be fixed later, but the developers seem to have no idea where they're going with the game, focusing on large procedurally generated universes (where did we see this before...) and pointless ship cosmetics 