76561198061539350,Recommended,244770,15571947,"Posted: 26 April, 2015",all,CmdrCade,"WARNING: IF YOU HAVE AN INTEL DRIVER ON YOUR COMPUTER, THIS WILL NOT START WITHOUT SOME FIDDLING AROUND.If you're like me, you have an Intel card and a Nvidia card. To get this to launch correctly, you must open your Nvidia control panel and go to ""manage 3D settings"". Once there, click on the program settings tab, and find Starmade in the drop first drop down. Then click on the second drop down and find  the High-Preformance NVIDIA proccessor option. Then click apply, exit, and run Starmade!As for other ghraphic cards, I have no idea. I've only ever used NVIDIA so I wouldn't know :/As for the game itself, lots of fun! Its kinda like Starbound 3D. You build awesome space ships, fight pirates, gather resources, and even land on 3D planets with their own gravity!All in all, if this game starts it is alot of fun. :D"
