76561198081422229,Recommended,244770,18731199,"Posted: 28 October, 2015",all,Oso De La Muerte,"The most accessible space building game yet.I highly recommend this game to anyone who enjoys the theme of space. I've spent a few hours on this game with a friend of mine, she and I trecked through space in what could only be described as a ""Miner's Life"". Due to the game being far from complete, it is without question that methods of income are highly limited. The game begins you off with only a few blocks, the essentials for a hopeful star-merchant or space-hero, the basic thrusters, some cannons, a core for your ship, power supply blocks and some armors. Being a new-found space explorer, it is without question that chasing down pirates it THE stupidest thing you can attempt. ( Although it may be possible to successfully bring down a pirate at the start. )Each system is a bit complex but it doesn't mean they are impossible for beginners to learn.Power System suggestion: DO NOT CLUMP YOUR POWER SUPPLIES! It's ineffective.The way the power supply works, I found it highly effective to line your system up in two 1 x X (X being any number you can afford ) lines that are spaced by one block each. So your systems would look like this:--------------------------------------------------   Each dash being power blocks.I'm not adept enough to figure out how the weapons systems work but from my research they're highly ineffective when clumped. I've seen a lot of suggestions stating that thirty cannon block separate and independent of each other are far more effective than all of them combined. Making bigger cannons practically useless.Also included in this game is a crafting system which I have not personally tested, it allows for the mined raw materials to be crafted into processed variants.Also worth noting: Each star CAN be approached. It's a matter of designing a ship that won't be obliterated by the time you reach it. Planets can be approached as well and even be built on to house a base or landing dock for the miners and would-be pirates.There are still a lot of systems that are implemented that I haven't even touched. A lot being complex or lacking an updated guide. For example: Turret systems, boarding systems, in depth power supplies, and as I've said before, weapons sytems.It is a game worth checking out and I highly suggest trying it with a friend."
