,Recommended,244770,13302940,"Posted: 10 December, 2014",all,Deadjack,"First of all I would like to say...WOW!Ok this is a space Minecraft style sandbox game but for a fresh release on early access on Steam...it's amazing !THE LAYOUT:After a quick tutorial (some aspects of the game are still missing...), you start near a ""cotton bud"" looking space station.You are an astronaut and with few credits and items you are left in a huge universe.First you have few blocks to build a basic spaceship. If you are smart enough, you will be able to go anywhere and enjoy the huge number of planets, asteroids and stations you can find (nearly infinite).THE GAMEPLAY:Ship and stations designs are easy. By pressing Space after entering a Ship core, you can launch building mode.The Ship core it some kind of box where the player can enter and control the ship.It's a strange way to use vehicles but the designer is enough well made to compensate this strange design.Like in Minecraft you use blocks, you place them with left click and delete with right click (you have tons of other contols by pressing left ctrl).For every ships, you have to plan it's energy usage and mass.The bigger the more expensive it will be for you: like the cloak wich needs more energy depending of the size  of the ship. The interresting aspect of this mode is the way you use weapons and tools.Every items needs a computer to be used. You put an appropriate computer and the weapon or tool block related, and you conect them. The funny thing is that you can mix weapons and some upgrade blocks to change their effects, like EMP or Shield Drain, ect...You can even place turret docking blocks with AI blocks to create an automated sentry capable to fire anything you want from missiles to beams.For tools you have less possibilities but you can put more blocks and computers to create massive Salvage beams (some kind of mining laser) or even create you own Antenna relay to scan your sector and spot anything that moves.You can even hold personnal weapons or tools (you have a basic mining laser) but you can't upgrade it much, like for the ships.You can also place a building block on a planet or a location you own ( with a faction block), to customize it.From the plants to the soils, being able to change a planet so quickly is excellent and gives you plenty ways to create.But you can't harvest materials by this way, you have to clear a path with the editor and go mining yourself.About crafting, it's not a good aspect of the game. Because you have too much materials and it becomes quickly too complicate to build nice recipes (bad crafting menus when you use crafting stations). In fact you will spare tons of time by harvesting raw materials and selling them to the Galatic Traders. These guys are the owners of the ""space cotton buds"" They are neutral npc that sells all blocks you can imagine and they buy everything you can bring !When you got the way to gather quickly, you get quite a lot of credits (the actual currency in the game).But space is a dangerous place...Players can be hostiles, you will notice that with a nice Faction system. By yourself you can create a faction, claim locations in its name and even conquer other players properties. Before doing that you need faction points with the help of other faction members and enough fights against enemy factions. This system is really good and surprises by it's quality for an early acess game.But your not alone because some pirates are roaming...They hide in somes big space stations with heavy turrets that does quite a lot of damage.But if you can manage to enter them... you will get tons of items !Be ware pirates are fliying in fast ships and dying is quite normal when you begin.Don't forget to buy enough stuff to build few basic ships when you first spawn.And find a nice planet to land.At this moment you will have time to study the blocks, the ways you have to earn money and CONQUER THE UNIVERS !TO CONCLUDE:Starmade is a real surprise. Quite impressive and cheap (the price will change), the gameplay it offers is amazing for an early acess.Ok i have to admit the game is rough around the edges: need some balance about the trade and crafting system. The tutorial wich is empty especially in front of game mechanics such as Factions or Logics. The physic for ship flights needs to be better because it's like driving in a ""soapbox"" or the punch of weapons wich are a bit weak especially on foot. Physic on blocks would be cool, like on some planets where lava ""floats"" in the airs.But the overall quality is really good for this kind of game, the developpers are even planing to add creatures (actually there is one alien spider you can see in the tutorial). And seriously, being able to build so much crazy things with turrets, landing zones, weapons, antenna and even warp gates...it's amazing !N.B: The game is quite stable, even if i had to play it on an old computer.You can also play alone on a dedicated server and set the difficulty of the AI. Life in space has never been so easy !"
