76561198058222764,Recommended,244770,27764340,"Posted: 26 November, 2016",all,Drake,"This game is really an awesome game. I waited quite a while to write this review. From the outside it might look like minecraft in space, but it is not.Starmade is a randomly generated huge universe, multiplayer or singleplayer, PVP, PVE, space simulation, sandbox game. That statement may seem like too much, but it does not do the game justice. I've been playing starmade for years. For a long time I played free via their website, but finally decided to buy it and support them. The game has gradually been changing, and is constantly being worked on. They are always listening to their forums for ideas in developing the game to better suit the players, but still keeping their core elements of the game alive.The most impressive aspect of the game to me is its builder or build mode. The build mode in starmade allows for players to do much more than just place blocks. It gives you shape outlines to use, you can set planes to create symmetry on structures, you can place blocks in many ways, and replace certain types with other types. The complexity may seem like a lot to get used to, but it is not you can hop right in, and the tutorials give you enough information to be building your own ship in minutes.The game also is constantly changing with great plans in place for future gameplay. Currently there are areas of the game that are lacking, but those areas are already being filled in. Even in the current state of the game, I find myself wasting many hours on it. It's definitely worth looking into if you like space exploration, combat, or even rpg elements. This game will have them all. Currently it's most lacking in rp elements, but there are plans to have quests and many other rp elements added in later. The game operates on a small server platform, so you can play online with friends or do local play to play by yourself.My Pros:Infinite Open Universe SimulationSandboxCompletely customizableBuild Ships, Spacestations, and Planet BasesBeautiful graphicsBlueprints to save created structuresMultiplayer or SingleplayerCreative or SurvivalInteresting Building MechanicsGreat combat with playersCons:AI is hilariously glitchy at timesCurrently in developmentSometimes can lag due to needed server optimizationPirates sometimes kill you before you can get established"
