,Recommended,244770,24963451,"Posted: 16 August, 2016",all,Muerks,"Don't let my play time on steam fool you.I've been playing this game on and off since it was just a rough idea in 2012 and only shortly have bought it via steam.Things improved a lot over the years and are getting better and better.After a long way this game is for the type of people loving to be creative and invest some serious time in a game.There is not too much grinding but be aware, you'll need to mine and craft :)The game is voxel based, so everythig can be changed.Technical issues:Well there are some minor things but it does not keep you from playing and enjoying the game.The only thing, which is not mentionned too clearly is that this game uses java.For the people that are having issues with the game, be sure to install the adequate java version!64bit windows goes with 64bit Java!!! After installing the 64bit Java, change the memory allocation in the starting client to a higher value.For the people still running a 32bit OS I'll say that they should not expect too much and the game will not run too smoothly as it really needs some horsepower :)For me most issues like crashes and freezes or stuttering vanished after installing the right version of Java.********Graphics:Here we stick with nice clean graphics, not too fancy but it gets the job well done.*********Sound:Sound is OK, but I guess it will be better in a while.********Gameplay:The gameplay is really good and once you understand how to control things everything falls into place and you get accustomed very fast to the controls.********If you like building, crafting, being creative and many other things, this game really could be for you.There is no recipe mechanic, everythig is build via different constructors, so no need to wiki for this :)Yes there are logic blocks and yes there are a lot of other good ideas :)And btw, don't get overwhelmed by the shear scope of the game, start small, try some stuff and progress slowly.You can try the demo version at first to get a feel for the game and after you spend a lot of hours you'll probably, like me, buy the game ;)Run your own server and play with your friends, you'll see, the world is a big place and you don't have to be alone."
