,Recommended,244770,13453553,"Posted: 19 December, 2014",all,Double Deuce,"Get. This. Game.It's easy to get into, and deceptively complex.  For example, they have logic blocks, aoe triggers, effects (on pretty much everything from lights to weapons) that you can do all kinds of  things with.  Those are  just a few examples.The game is freaking huge...not sure if it ever ends tbh...so many sectors in a system, systems  in a galaxy, galaxies in π and you have 42 (Gorilla math was used).The exploration is like a box of chocolates.  You could find a random shop to buy and sell  things, you could find a pirate station with turrets and ships attacking you, or asteroids, and I even hear you can find  a city but I've yet to find one.  There's planets and asteroids to mine, stations to build,  ships of every kind to make.  There's cloaking, radar jamming, scanning, jump drive (warping / long distance travel), push / pull weapons (tractor beam anyone?), drainers of all types, cannons, missiles, you name it, they probably have it.You can save your ship designs locally and on servers (multiplayer) and load them onto  another server using blueprints.  Think template that you fill with all the components and when the blueprint has all the parts it  needs you can spawn it.  You can build bases and outposts, or repair undiscovered /  unclaimed stations and  claim them as your own  / build on it.  There's factions (corps  / guilds) and every faction gets to claim 1 home base which is invincible to damage unless  they run  out of faction points (hard to do unless you claim alot of systems or die alot),Very customizable server settings so each multiplayer server you play on is probably different from every other.  You can customize your singleplayer server.cfg as well if you so choose.The cons:This is more on the servers you play on but when there's alot of people it tends to lag / warp.  (It's Alpha).  The initial RAM settings for the game is 1024  which  is really low.  If you are on a  64 bit OS you will want to download the 64 bit Java and change the RAM settings.  You can do this by going to the menu in the launcher > Options > Memory settingsI have 16GB RAM so I changed mine to 8192 1000 1000  and I stopped getting running out of memory errors  in game.  You will also most likely want to disable procedural background if you get alot of lag...caused me several seconds delay getting out of my ships in high pop servers.  All these options can be changed in the launcher, there's also advanced settings in  the launcher.All in all, this is a very fun game I would highly recommend it and I would buy it again.  I figured sooner or later there wont be a free demo and the price will most likely go up so why not support the devs now and not have to worry about it later on.Get in a faction with people or with friends as this amplifies the fun factor 10 fold.11/10 would buy again."
76561198125050476,Recommended,244770,24561820,"Posted: 27 July, 2016",all,Maltheus,"My favorite part of Minecraft was being able to build complex redstone creations to automate all sorts of things. If that's what you liked most about it, then this game is definitely for you. You can set up factories to automatically refine what you collect into pretty much any block in the game. The stack sizes are huge and you can expand the storage space of a ""chest"" as large as you'd like. So if you were into collecting large amounts of stuff in Minecraft, then you'll appreciate how much easier it is to manage here.The best thing about this game to me is the design/blueprint system. When you have a shipyard, you can create a design using creative mode, and then it'll tell you what blocks you need to construct it. You can save off that design to a blueprint and import it to another server or single player game. It's like having WorldEdit built into the normal course of the game.Pros:* One of, if not the best, building systems I've ever seen.* Ability to create huge ships and stations.* Lots of potential for automation.* The ability to save/import blueprints.* Good assortment of blocks to work with.Cons:* High learning curve.* Wikis are sparse, meaning you have to hunt through youtube videos to figure stuff out.* Pirates are devastating for new players. I had to cheat (ie. use creative) to get that first decent ship built. If I hadn't I would have given up on it. Could probably do it now without cheating, but it would take too long.* Some of the controls are inconsistent. Like shift slows you down, unless you're in build mode, then it speeds you up. Sometimes you use Q to go up, other times space.* Ran into a few issues getting it to run on Linux. Almost gave up (glad I didn't).Before this game, I was playing a lot of Elite Dangerous on a Vive. Better graphics and virtual reality were not enough to keep me entertained like StarMade has so far. I wish it were a little more popular, but it has enough for me to play for years, just as it is now. If you can make do without a large multiplayer community (I play SP), and you like building, then I highly recommend it."
