,Recommended,244770,29470448,Posted: 24 January,all,mapppa,"Don't be fooled by my playtime as I usually play without using steam.Pros:* Excellent ship building. This game probably outshines many other games when it comes to building. It has many tools to make building a lot faster and easier* Multi-player. Even though it can lag in larger ship battles, starmade probably provides the best multi-player experience of all space building games out there. It's especially fun to build and explore with friends on a server. It also provides to ability to run dedicated server for both linux and windows.* Scale. No other game provides this kind of scale. The biggest ships in other games wouldn't even be considered medium sized ships in this games. There are also some extremely beautiful ships made my the community from all kinds of franchises* Great weapon system. Weapons can be combined and used in a lot of different ways. It's very fun to play around with it. It's however a bit imbalanced at the moment for PvP, but that is to be expected of a game in alpha* Logic Systems and Rails. This feature is one of the best. You can virtually build anything. The rail system allows for complex doors, elevators, and countless other mechanisms. The logic systems lets you control you build things from simple light switches to password protected doors to even crazier stuff like space monopoly.* Fleets. Although a bit buggy at the moment, the fleet system allows you to bring your own carriers into battle.* NPCs. The new update provided lots of gameplay for single and multi-player and finally made the universe feel a lot more aliveCons:* The game is still in alpha and that shows at several points in the game. Some features need polishing or more work and there are some bugs. However the devs have announced they will address these issues.* Depending on your playstyle there is not much to do after a certain point in singleplayer. The NPC update did help with that, but there more is needed, and 