76561198015456313,Recommended,244770,13887145,"Posted: 7 January, 2015",all,hellbiter88,"This game has lego style blocks, starships, stars, warp drives and BLACK HOLES!That ^^^^ right there is enough for me to recommend this game. HOWEVER: Note that this game is still incomplete, and it shows. As much as I love what's going on here and the raw potential this game has, note that there's some issues, read: many issues, yet to be resolved. For example, Travel is unbelievably slow. You can easily change this by editing a text file (google ""How to increase Starmade speed limit""), but this is not something a noob like me would even know was possible, let alone standard. Also, the planets currently have no mobs that spawn, so apart from gathering resources here and there, selling them, building a ship, travelling about, and I suppose fighting pirates or joining a server, there isn't much to do. At least it feels that way after awhile. Other stuff needs to be added to make it more engaging. Also, I do not like the crafting system at all, and find that I have much more fun just using console commands to acquire items and building my own ship creative mode-style.But all-in-all, yes, I recommend this game. I'm having fun with it--just know that if you're the type who doesn't like building things.. this game is definitely something to reconsider."
