,Recommended,244770,16218168,"Posted: 5 June, 2015",all,ClayXros (Plain Cereal),"I think I've played enough to throw my perverbial hat into the ring.This game is in effect Minecraft crossed with a successful space sim game. This is a gross simplification, for it is simply it's own entitiy.You are able to creat in effect any spacecraft, space station, or even ship should you desire under the sun (thnks to various wedges and such) as well as pages of materials to build from, including many aesthetic blocks. Weapons too are able to be customized to your combat style, be it a close up shotgun or long range explosive sniper cannon, you have the ability to make it. It even has a stealth system. (I myself am working on a modified Normandy from Mass effect) The galaxy (or depending on the server, galaxies) are massive in scope, and even on a fully populated server you can find a place to set up your base.Crafting is also fairly straightforward. Collect ores, pop them in a refinery, combine them by connecting factories to create a manufacture line. Very efficient. The building aspect even comes with a build mode, as well as an advanced version that allows you to place/remove alot of blocks on your creation quickly.It does however have it's share of teething issues. Lighting glitches occur quite a bit, and the mini-radar is very ineffective in detecting threats until you're already space dust. The new rail system also has a few operation glitches, especially when creating hatches and large doorways within ships and space stations. (nothing crippling, just annoying on occasion) In the build mode there can be issues when palcing alot of blocks if you are not careful, and the ""build helper"" which assists with making circles is flat out useless. (cirlce is not a circle, and is not symmetrical at all. Making a sphere with it is impossible I tried)I know nothing of the communities, but the servers can be very dangerous. Pick a remote area and high tail it there if you wish to build in any sort of peace. (I play on Red-Shift, a large active server which gives you alot of credits so you can quickly make a defendable ship and starbase in a remote area)Overall, for the price this game is a bargain. The ship/station building system is the best I've seen, and space combat is challenging but fun. (especially with missles. BOOM) It has glitches and bugs, but given the scale of the game they can be ignored with relative content. (not that they shouldn't be fixed, obviously they should) The forums could use some better policing for trolls and ""neo-nazis"" harassing people who only wish to see the game grow. And this is just the Early Access! Imagine how good it will be at 1.0!My rating for this game is a solid 7/10. Amazing in scope and execution, however has a few issues that could be annoying to novice players of survival and space games."
