76561198042237959,Recommended,244770,13995169,"Posted: 15 January, 2015",all,ezdez,"If Minecraft is a sandbox, StarMade is the beach. And instead of getting a shovel, you're given a bulldozer. The way the weapon system works is great - if this were in minecraft, it'd be like strapping 4 bows to your arms, but instead of arrows you shoot pickaxes to mine faster. And do you like that epic mansion you built in singleplayer? Why not save the blueprint and rebuild it in multiplayer? All you need are the resources. AMAZING. What's more, the game is free. FREE. Go and try it out, then pay for the game anyway because it's damn fun.THESE DEVS CARE. Lots of updates, great community and massive potential. The game has a lot of great things in it, the core mechanics are solid and lots of different elements. Let's review some of the common comments:Great multiplayer - valid (this game is built for sharing with friends or strangers)Boring single player - mixed (there's not much ""to do"" other than fight pirates, build spaceships and mine resources. There wasn't much to do in Minecraft in Beta either. Quests are coming.Bugs - invalid (the game is free, try it first, and yeah it's an alpha)Real talk: you'll probably never build anything epic. You want to build the Enterprise? You won't. But you CAN download the blueprint. My only warning is that the game isn't optimised yet, and there are lag spikes even on recommended system requirements. Memory leaks are common in alphas and so I'm ok with this. Some funny bugs though, a trade guild convoy of about 5 ships crashed into a planet and was stuck. Dropped fps to about 1-5fps, practically unplayable, but also hilarious. Would lag again."
