,Recommended,244770,17051983,"Posted: 14 July, 2015",all,Izavar,"Eve meets Minecraft, the game excels at letting me fly lego-like starships that I used to make as a child. Lacks some UI refinement and some polished objectives if you're in singleplayer. Also, much of the building is very, very technical in nature, sometimes needing to run equations to understand power requirements of systems.Biggest innovation for the voxel-sandbox games - Integration of ""Creative Mode"" into gameplay through the ""core"" and ""build"" blocks. When you're building a ship, you start with a core block. You enter this block to build and fly the ship. In Build mode, it allows you to freely move the camera about, and even set planes to mirror building on the blocks.Resource collection and manufacturing of blocks is meant to be done at large scale, empowering (and enticing!) you to make capital-sized ships.Game is good now; I'd be really curious to see what it woudl be like if they applied some of the lessons from voxel games like Trove, with adding more user-tangible color and objectives to the mix."
