76561198031482198,Not Recommended,244770,14443837,"Posted: 13 February, 2015",all,Hellrazor,"The interface is terrible, the lag is terrible, the (default) controls are terrible. Get ready to notice that the devs haven't quite figured out the difference between ""breaking"" and ""braking"" - which is probably the least of their grammer, English, and general text formatting errors, There is an atmosphere in thevacuumof space, you'll constantly find yourself fighting to get oriented the right way due to the devs forcing an up and downIN SPACE(because screw logic), and the mouse sensitivity is insanely low by default (I've got it around 1.3, it starts at 0.5).The graphical options (which you find when you press 'Start Game', as opposed to 'Options...') are probably the most competent part of the entire game, which isn't saying much. The resolutions and refresh rates seem to be a fixed list (despite knowing for a fact that Java can poll the OS for a list of available screen resolutions and refresh rates); antialiasing and v-sync (competently named 'Vertical Synch') are hidden (check 'Settings->Show Advanced Settings' to get them), while anisotropic filtering is still AWOL; and the launcher is more than happy to bring your computer to a grinding halt to get you to the options menu in the first place (don't you just love Java?).As for the actual gameplay, you mostly find yourself wandering aimlessly and taking a long time (due to the aforementioned ""the vacuum of space, now with ∞% more atmosphere"") to get somewhere to do something so that you can make your tiny ship a little bigger, and continue rinsing and repeating.Noting that this is in early alpha, most of this is fixable, while some of it should have never been a problem in the first place. At the moment I'd recommend staying away."
