,Not Recommended,244770,13801512,"Posted: 2 January, 2015",all,Mojyo,"Ah, Starmade. Where to start, where to start...Let's start off with the fact that it isn't friendly at all to new users. Poorly laid-out tutorial and abstract navigation, in all aspects, hits a new player like a freight train. Not to mention the incredibly confusing movement mechanics, high learning curve, and lack of direction.Yes, it is a sandbox. Yes, there are such things as 'quests'. Yes, there is multiplayer, but it is so lacking in 'oomph' that, after playing a little while, you sit back and think ""What the hell am I accomplishing?"" The very existence of this thought is a red flag that maybe buying this game wasn't the best choice.Not to mention the voxel-based sandbox genre that's now getting kind of old. Yes, I knew when buying the game that it would have this 'style', but at the time I thought that it would be toned down a notch, like Space Engineers. Sadly, I was dead wrong. Not that I should complain, just a nitpick.StarMade, in its Alpha, has quite of a bit of a journey to make in its development.For now, StarMade sits in the dark corner of my game library, waiting to be re-installed when I feel like it's worthy of another try."
