,Recommended,244770,14185265,"Posted: 26 January, 2015",all,C0DA,"I keep trying to update this but it reverts :/First of all, i recommend this game to fans of construction based pvp games who have the patience to learn complex and unintuitive mechanics that rely on multi-tiered knowledge and rigorous multiplayer (so, latency conditioned) testing, it has solid building & engineering mechanics on top of satisfying combat depending on scale & complexity of designs used.Good combat is ephemeral however, a few poor design choices on behalf of only one combatant is enough to reduce fps to a slideshow and induce too much input lag for piloting skill to matter much at all.Community is highly fragmented, paranoia is rampant due to the games complexity and exploitability combined with a small playerbase.  Forumside cross talks is largely dominated by newer players and more solo/RP players who have little interest or understanding in balance at the meta end, Devs attempt to maintain contact with a knowledgable pvp base through other mediums but crosstalk and Agendas are infectious.Progress is slow, and not always in the right directions, I fear the devs are focusing too much on features being asked for forumside than the core gameplay mechanics required to actually enjoy such features.  A Modding API is often spoken of but in no way guaranteed.As it stands, the core gameplay mechanics are construction, combat and gathering/crafting.Which i would rate;Contruction; 7/10, new features are being released soon that may just make it a 10/10, however i expect bugs and dissappointment initially so wont jump the gun.Combat; 5/10,  Absolute blast when it works (when masses are reasonable, rail parts are minimal and functional and drones fleets are left at home), unplayable trash when it doesn't, which is all too easy for an inexperienced or malicious designer (like the ones responsible for the official god damn stations & NPC ships for ♥♥♥♥s sake, test this trash first)Crafting/Gathering; 2/10, repetitive grind, nothing worthy of praise here other than the fact that it has been far worse in the past and that schine acklowdges it.  Wupdydoo though, it's still trash.I deeply want to see this game succeed, it makes all other big space sandbox type games look like visionless trash.  But you should also note that some of those have working core mechanics and are more ready for late alpha/beta stage developement than Starmade, which is far older.Don't get attached (too late for me), but please give it a try, and leave as honest and well tested feedback as you can, schine and all of us waiting on them will thank you for it. (btw you can just download it for free during its alpha phase, directly from their website, you do not have to purchase the game just yet to play it fully)"
