,Recommended,244770,15216275,"Posted: 5 April, 2015",all,TheMetalOne,"Very cool concept. All things considered, I'd say it's pretty well done too.Stepping into the game is a bit overwhelming. The tutorial throws a lot of info at you pretty fast, and due to typos and some parts that are poorly explained, you may find yourself scratching your head thinking ""wtf am i supposed to do?""Stick with it.This game is basically Minecraft in space. However, where Minecraft doesn't really have any direction to it, this game does. Minecraft is a hodge podge of whatever stuff the devs thought might be cool to have, this game is all about mining and crafting for the purpose of building space ships. You can do more than that, but it all comes back to the ships. Due to the amount of creativity that it possible with the building system, this is NOT a bad thing.I have barely scratched the surface of all the possibilities this game provides, and I'm already having fun. Building ships is fun. The crafting is interesting. The exploring can leave you with genuine feelings of intrigue when you come across a new planet.There are downsides, however. I did experience repeated crashes caused by an error that was only able to be resolved by reinstalling the game. The launcher does streamline this process, though. The tutorial needs another look, especially the typos in it, as they make an already confusing subject matter that much more confusing. The controls are pretty clunky. It's kind of born out of necessity, though, because there are a lot of actions that each need a key. My personal recommendation would be for the devs to remove some of the less necessary actions (can't remember an example off the top of my head, but i know i saw some) and implement the ability to customize keybindings ASAP to lessen the awkwardness.All in all, this is literally the only early access game i have ever played that I felt was worth the money, and fully entertaining this early in developement. It's also the only early access game i have ever clicked the ""yes, i recommend this"" button for in a review. I spent almost 2 hours in this game, and it felt like 20 mins. Very engaging, and I look forward to seeing great things from this game. If you're on a budget, you can play the alpha for free. Just know that this game is worth the current price of $9 in it's current state, so buying it while it's cheap could be a really good deal. The devs have said the price will go up as features are added, and the game nears completion, so bear that in mind if you like it."
