76561198123408793,Recommended,244770,15148134,"Posted: 31 March, 2015",all,Blazikinahat,"So, I have played this game for a few hours now and i have to say it is an excellent game for early access. Although it may feel like minecraft, it is NOT minecraft. It has a few bugs that need to be figured out and I think I would prefer an actual in game engine. It definitly be better optimized for mac, which by the way I suggest getting this game for PC and not Mac. The developers may have fixed optimization for mac for some bugs but, it still falls flat. Especially when I try running it on my mac. It either crashes or is slow starting up or when I actually manage get it running mac the framerate is all over the place. If you plan to get this game I recommend you get it but run it on PC because mac simply doesn't run very well especially this early. I would like to add that this game is stingy when it comes to RAM. Allow me to explain: My PC has an intel extreme motherboard, a Geforce GT 9800, and 8GB of RAM(it had 4). When I upgraded to 8GB from for the reason was because the game said to and I quote ""increase the max memory."" Of course I upgrade to 8GB(it was time anyway). So, I upgraded and I got the same message just after I upgraded. Please fix this. The messages are annoying especially when it should have fixed itself with the upgrade. PS: if anyone has any thoughts on trying to get a quick fix, I welcome the assistance.UPDATE: I haven't played this game in weeks and I wanted to give a quick update for my review. I have change my rating of this game from recommend to not recommend. Why? because they changed the price to $14.99. That price is simply not reasonable especially for a game that isn't nearly complete nor does it have a proper starting menu! It has planets to explore but no creatures to fight. I don't use muliplayer but the last time I tried to the servers kept craching on me. Until, they can have thi game no longer in beta, I DO NOT Recommend this game. I will keep my copy and update it as they roll out but, I will not be playing his game unil it has come out of beta. Also, my mac isn't the most powerful thing the world and my PC the one with 9800 GT doesn't show picture anymore so, I need a new PC to play this game anyway. In addition, the recommended specs and minimum specs listed are too vague to even consider trying the game out.UPDATE 4/7/2016: I am recommending this game because I have found a way to fix the RAM issue that I had earlier. I would have prefered NOT to edit the amount of RAM allocated as I thought it would be automatic, but it works and that is what matters now. I am very pleased with the recent updates to the logic system and I hope that more will roll out as I continue my support for this game as it has a lot of potential. I hope that a new launcher gets introduced as soon as possible and that future players won't have to edit the RAM allocation as most games have it on automatic anyway. I hope that new detail options, new ship templates and new Space Station templates to give more creativity and options. I would also like to see a small drop in price as $14.99 is still a bit much for a game in beta. I still stand by my thoughts on the price as said in the previous update. So until the next update, buy this game to let your creative mind loose.UPDATE 3/10/2017: Now that the main menu has gotten a major overhall, and the game has gotten some major improvements I still keep my review of this game to recommended. Now, it isn't perfect but, I never expected it to be. With the massive improvements to the menu and an easier way to allocate memory to the game it seem like once the game game is finished I will be playing more and more. Keep up the good work. Also, for those interested in early access on steam this is how you do it. This is an excellent example of how to do EA."
